 {"id":"franken_networkx-zzcm4","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: ancestors and descendants reject undirected graphs unlike NetworkX","description":"The wide parity matrix found fnx.ancestors and fnx.descendants raise NetworkXError on undirected Graph and MultiGraph fixtures while upstream NetworkX returns reachable-node sets using the graph's adjacency semantics.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T02:49:11.619217695Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T02:49:11.619217695Z","close_reason":"Completed: ancestors and descendants now support undirected graph families by returning the reachable component minus the source, and missing-node errors now match NetworkX graph/digraph wording. Wide parity matrix now passes these cells.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-zzcm5","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: pagerank weighted and MultiGraph parity gaps","description":"The wide parity matrix found pagerank value divergences from upstream NetworkX on weighted undirected graphs and MultiGraph inputs. Root-cause likely sits in weight projection and parallel-edge aggregation semantics.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T03:25:13.882356412Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T03:25:13.882356412Z","close_reason":"Completed: pagerank now honors signed edge weights for simple graphs and sums parallel-edge weights for MultiGraph/MultiDiGraph projections before running the native PageRank iteration. Wide parity matrix now passes the weighted and multigraph pagerank cells.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"franken_networkx-zzcm6","title":"[HIGH] REVIEW: unweighted shortest-path wrappers reject directed graphs","description":"The wide parity matrix found single_source_shortest_path, single_source_shortest_path_length, all_pairs_shortest_path, and all_pairs_shortest_path_length raise NetworkXNotImplemented on directed graph fixtures where upstream NetworkX returns directed shortest-path results.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z","created_by":"codex","updated_at":"2026-04-24T03:43:35.273654356Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T03:43:35.273654356Z","close_reason":"Completed: unweighted single-source and all-pairs shortest-path wrappers now dispatch directed graphs through directed BFS helpers instead of rejecting them. Wide parity matrix now passes the directed shortest-path cells.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
