+{"id": "franken_networkx-zzcm7", "title": "[HIGH] REVIEW: directed component and topological error contracts diverge", "description": "The wide parity matrix found strongly_connected_components yields SCCs in a different order from upstream NetworkX on directed fixtures. It also found topological_sort on a cyclic digraph raises HasACycle where upstream raises NetworkXUnfeasible.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z", "created_by": "codex", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:58:49.422775Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:58:49.422775Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: SCC emits in nx sink-first order; topological_sort/generations/lexicographic raise NetworkXUnfeasible (not HasACycle) on cyclic input."}
+{"id": "franken_networkx-zzcm8", "title": "[HIGH] REVIEW: local_bridges graph-family rejection contracts diverge", "description": "The wide parity matrix found local_bridges returns results on directed graphs and MultiGraph inputs where upstream NetworkX raises NetworkXNotImplemented.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z", "created_by": "codex", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:58:49.422775Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:58:49.422775Z", "close_reason": "Fixed: local_bridges raises NetworkXNotImplemented on directed and multigraph inputs, matching @not_implemented_for decorator."}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-zzcm9", "title": "[HIGH] REVIEW: MultiGraph structural algorithms diverge from NetworkX", "description": "The wide parity matrix found MultiGraph-specific structural gaps: is_tree and is_forest return true despite parallel edges where upstream returns false; bridges includes the parallel edge pair that upstream excludes; degree_centrality undercounts parallel-edge degree; complement raises TypeError where upstream returns a MultiGraph complement.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T00:56:26.319497097Z", "created_by": "codex", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:48:54.137026Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:48:54.137026Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in cycle-continuation commit: Python overrides for is_tree/is_forest/bridges/degree_centrality/complement on MultiGraph input match nx contract (count parallels, exclude parallel-edge bridges, delegate complement to nx for MG)."}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-grid2d", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] grid_2d_graph node type is str instead of tuple", "description": "fnx.grid_2d_graph(m, n) delegates to Rust fast path when create_using is None and m/n are ints. Rust emits node labels as strings like \"0,0\" whereas nx uses tuples (0,0). Breaks drop-in: G[(0,0)] raises KeyError on fnx. Python fallback is already correct. Fix: bypass Rust fast path.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in 923177e: grid_2d_graph Python fallback preserves tuple nodes"}
 {"id": "franken_networkx-hypcub", "title": "REVIEW: [HIGH] hypercube_graph node type is int instead of tuple of bits", "description": "fnx re-exports hypercube_graph directly from Rust. nx.hypercube_graph(n) returns nodes labeled as tuples of n 0/1 ints (e.g. (0,0,0)); fnx returns integer labels 0..2^n-1. Breaks drop-in: G[(0,0,0)] raises KeyError. Fix: Python wrapper matching nx.", "status": "closed", "priority": 1, "issue_type": "bug", "created_at": "2026-04-24T03:42:56.094028Z", "created_by": "cc-networkx", "updated_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "closed_at": "2026-04-24T04:34:16.823011Z", "close_reason": "Fixed in 923177e: hypercube_graph Python wrapper emits bit tuples"}
